    Eac h of thefactors shou ld be listed number of times  correspon d ing to how many times it app ea res in factorization.    Input numbershould be equal t o the product of all  fact ors
    >>> factorize(8)
    [2, 2, 2]
    >>> factorize(25)
    [5, 5]
    >>> factorize(70)
    [2, 5, 7]
     */
    public List<Integer> factorize(int n) {

canonical_solution:
        List<Integer> fact = new ArrayList<>();
        int i = 2;
        while (n > 1) {
            if (n % i == 0) {
                fact.add(i);
                n /= i;
            } else {
                i++;
            }
        }
        return fact;
    }
}

